page.title: 05A HUNDRED YEARS AGO.
page.content:
Extracts from the 'Cambridge Chronicle' of 1885:
17th April. On Wednesday Mr. C.W.Palmer,County Coroner,held an inquest at Haslingfield upon the body of Edward Palmer,aged 84.He complained of a pain in his side.
6th November. Mr.Chas. Hale QC addressed a meeting in this village on Friday evening in a barn kindly lent by Mr. East of Willow Farm. (M. Prime).
LANDOWNERS IN 1851(?). Reverend Stephen Allen,John Bangle, John Bond,Edward Dale,Earl de la Warr, Richard Foster,Jane Hall,Jonathan Hall,James(?) Mitchell,Robert Prime, John Titmarsh,Robert Webb.(M.Kipping).
